 {\cf1 29}The Philistines had assembled their forces at Aphek, and the Israelites encamped by the fountain in Jezreel. {\super\cf2\fs24 2}The lords of the Philistines were marching past, with hundreds and with thousands, and David and his men marched in the rear guard with Achish. {\super\cf2\fs24 3}Then the commanders of the Philistines said, \uc1\u8220*What are these Hebrews doing here?\uc1\u8221* And Achish said to the commanders of the Philistines, \uc1\u8220*This is David, the servant of Saul the king of Israel, who has now been with me two years, and I have found no fault in him from the time that he came over to me to the present.\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 4}But the commanders of the Philistines were enraged against him, and said, \uc1\u8220*Send back the man so that he may return to the place where you have stationed him. Don\uc1\u8217*t let him go down with us to battle \uc1\u8211* he might become an adversary to us. How could this fellow better ingratiate himself with his master than with the heads of our men? {\super\cf2\fs24 5}Is this not the David of whom they sang responsively in the dances, saying,
