 {\super\cf2\fs24 11}They found an Egyptian in the field and brought him to David and gave him food to eat and water to drink, {\super\cf2\fs24 12}and they gave him a piece of fig cake, and two clusters of raisins. When he had eaten, his spirit revived, for he had eaten no bread and drunk no water for three days and nights. {\super\cf2\fs24 13}David said to him, \uc1\u8220*To whom do you belong? Where are you from?\uc1\u8221* He said \uc1\u8220*I am an Egyptian lad, an Amalekite\uc1\u8217*s servant, and my master abandoned me because three days ago I fell sick. {\super\cf2\fs24 14}We made a raid upon the South Country of the Cherethites and on that which belongs to Judah and upon the South Country of Caleb, and Ziklag we burned down.\uc1\u8221* {\super\cf2\fs24 15}And David said to him, \uc1\u8220*Will you bring me down to this band?\uc1\u8221* He said, \uc1\u8220*Swear to me by God, that you will neither kill me nor deliver me into the hands of my master, and I will bring you down to this band.\uc1\u8221*
