{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi720 
 {\super\cf2\fs24 8}When on the following day the Philistines came to strip the slain, they found Saul and his three sons fallen on Mount Gilboa. {\super\cf2\fs24 9}They cut off his head and stripped off his armor and sent throughout the land of the Philistines to bring the good news to their idols and to the people. {\super\cf2\fs24 10}They put his armor in the temple of Ashtarte, and they fastened his body on the wall of Beth-shan. {\super\cf2\fs24 11}When the inhabitants of Jabesh in Gilead heard what the Philistines had done to Saul, {\super\cf2\fs24 12}all the valiant men arose and marched all night and took the bodies of Saul and his sons from the wall of Beths-han. They returned to Jabesh and burned them there. {\super\cf2\fs24 13}They took their bones and buried them under the tamarisk tree in Jabesh, and they fasted seven days.
